Experiment No.—1: Introduction to MySQL Environment 

a) Installation of Workbench or XAMPP server  
b) Create Database “College_DB” 
Check existing database 
Drop database 
c) Create a new MySQL user named college_user with password Password@123. 
• Create User 
• Check if user exist 
• Grant privileges to user  
• Drop existing User 

SHOW DATABASES;
Create DATABASES College_DB;
USE College_DB;
DROP Database College_DB;

CREATE USER 'college_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Password@123';
SELECT User, Host FROM mysql.user WHERE User = 'college_user';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON College_DB.* TO 'college_user'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
DROP USER 'college_user'@'localhost';
